main event: On July 24, 1953, USAF pilots observed a luminous object in a rapid, erratic motion over Key West, Florida.
interesting points: The object was described as elongated and visible for approximately 3 1/2 minutes,The object was initially compared to a star but was determined to be something else upon closer observation,The object blinked on and off and showed variations in motion,Interviews indicated that the observers were deemed reliable with above-average reputations,The conclusion of the sightings suggested the possibility of being searchlights or other explainable phenomena.
